     \DiagramSquare {
       nw = \pi _1^*E,
       sw = B\times B,
       se = B,
       ne = E,
       east/style = {|->},
       west/style = {|->,exists},
       north/style = {->,exists},
       south = \pi _1,
       height = 1.5cm,
     }
     \qquad 
     \DiagramSquare {
       nw = \pi _2^*F,
       sw = B\times B,
       se = B,
       ne = F,
       east/style = {|->},
       west/style = {|->,exists},
       north/style = {->,exists},
       south = \pi _2,
       height = 1.5cm,
     }



   The above can be seen as cartesian lift in the 2-bifibration of fibered categories over \mathbf {Cat}.

Finally, we take a cocartesian lift along the tensor functor {B\times B}\xrightarrow {{\otimes }}{B} to obtain the Day tensor:





